    "created_at": "2015-12-18T20:28:09Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-12-18T20:28:09Z",
    "body": "Native menus _are_ customizable, so what you're actually offering is a single, fixed native menu implementation.\n\nBeing able to change the color of a menu is important in Windows. Very few applications on Windows leave the default menu bar color as the default, so Electron is practically useless for people wanting to build Windows apps that look nice.\n\nWithout this feature, there's no reason for me to use Electron because I'll have to re-implement menus in HTML to make them look good. If I actually want a _good looking_ native app, I might as well just use WinForms with either CefSharp or the WebBrowser control.\n"
  },
  {
