      "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/waynebloss/received_events",
      "type": "User",
      "site_admin": false
    },
    "created_at": "2015-12-18T20:32:39Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-12-18T20:32:39Z",
    "body": "The question should not be _can we implement it so it's cross platform_ in my opinion.\n\nThe question should be _is it important to implement on any platform_ and the answer to that is yes. It's important for Windows.\n\nIt's not important for OS X because OS X menus are not part of the application window. Therefore, the system colors don't clash with the visual style of the window.\n\nIf you always choose the lowest common denominator, Electron won't be a hybrid environment worth using and it will suck on all platforms kind of like the web in general.\n"
  },
