    "created_at": "2015-12-19T02:20:01Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-12-19T02:20:20Z",
    "body": "It's a standard and widely used feature for high level Windows desktop SDKs though. Saying that it's custom or owner-drawn doesn't mean much IMO, when it amounts to one or two simple setting for background/foreground color and maybe a third one for a background image.\n\nThe code I'm looking at for searches like [win32 change menu color](https://www.google.com/search?q=win32+change+menu+color) doesn't seem terribly difficult.\n\nI guess the bottom line is, if you don't want to do the work because you think it's too much effort to add a few Menu properties that are only useful on Windows - would you consider looking at pull requests to add such a feature?\n"
  },
