    "created_at": "2015-12-19T03:06:47Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-12-19T03:06:47Z",
    "body": "Here's an example using WinForms - I customized this window's menu, toolbar and splitters by setting BackgroundColor and ForeColor to a different system color. Other than that, I had to do very little work to make a decent \"dark mode\". If I wanted to get this basic feature in Electron, I'd have to build a whole menu system with HTML/CSS/JS.\n\n(The main content block there is a WebBrowser control that points to this [chrome-tabs demo](http://adamschwartz.co/chrome-tabs/).)\n\n![2015-12-18 21_54_24-darkmenudemo](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/623736/11910916/05867986-a5d3-11e5-94e2-dd454b326c4b.png)\n\n![2015-12-18 21_54_34-settings](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/623736/11910917/09c8b4dc-a5d3-11e5-8c9f-b1a7737d9c4b.png)\n\nSo that's my final argument for this topic. I understand if you don't want to do the work, but I would like to know if you'll consider pull requests for a feature or two like this. Thanks for all your efforts.\n\nOff-topic - I'd really like to see icons in menus too.\n"
  },
